column3: I've been using 1.0.1c for my own Windows builds for months and have not found any problems with it.\n

Automatic sanity-testing: FAILED BUILD/TEST, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/b7a8802c2acd61394b63856d7ff7ca942df81a00 for binaries and test log.

This could happen for one of several reasons:
1. It chanages paths in makefile.linux-mingw or otherwise changes build scripts in a way that made them incompatible with the automated testing scripts
2. It does not build on either Linux i386
Please increase the deps version number, ie to bitcoin-deps-0.0.5.zip (both in deps-win32.yml and gitian-win32.yml)\n

Closing this. \nWill merge all into a single commit in a new pull.\n
You don't need to close your pull for that. You can just "rebase -i", squash the commits and push -f to the current branch.\n

I would have. But those commits were in the master branch, instead of a separate one. I've been meaning to start using branches for pulls for a while now, so thought I might just sort myself out and do that instead.\n
1.0.0c build for pull-tester, should test properly now.\n
We are at 1.50 for Windows AFAIK? Perhaps you can create another small patch for this.\n
I think 1.5.0 is not the same thing as 1.50.0.\n
